PER CURIAM:Â  Horace Rodney Bell pled guilty to possession with intent to distribute cocaine.Â  He was sentenced to seven years, suspended upon the service of eighteen months, plus two years probation.Â  Bellâ€™s appellate counsel filed a brief pursuant to Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738 (1967).Â  Counsel additionally submitted a petition to be relieved from representation, asserting there are no directly appealable issues of arguable merit.Â  Bell did not file a pro se response with the Court.
After a review of the record pursuant to Anders and State v. Williams, 305 S.C. 116, 406 S.E.2d 357 (1991), we dismiss the appeal and grant counselâ€™s petition to be relieved.[1]
